    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012098>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Diagnostic characters of Bolbapium. (a). Dorsal view, five striae between the suture and the humeral callus; (b). subtrapezoidal clypeus; (c). trituberculated clypeo-frontal suture." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012098/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012104>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Bolbapium (a). Hind wings. Apex of the third branch of the radial vein directed towards the outer edge of the wing (black setae 1); between the cubital and the first anal vein articulated with the base of the wing there are two free veins (black circle); jugular wing area is not reduced (black setae 2). (b). Antenna with the last three antennomeres elongated. (c). Antenna with the last three antennomeres globose." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012104/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012106>
    dc:description "Figure 3. (a). Head with tranverse carina,Bolbapium striatopunctatum (Castelnau, 1840); (b). head with tranverse carina, Bolbapium dutraorum Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (c). clypeal-frontal carina high, pronotum with bituberculated structure, Bolbapium sergioidae Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (d). head with tubercles adjacent to each eye; pronotum with concave structure, Bolbapium luederwaldti Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (e). clypeal-frontal carina with very high and prominent central tubercle ♂, Bolbapium minutum (Luederwaldt, 1931); (f). pronotum mesoanteriorly with pair of longitudinal structure, Bolbapium baeri (Boucomont, 1902)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012106/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012128>
    dc:description "Figure 12. Geographical distribution. (a). Bolbapium baeri (Boucomont, 1902) (white circle) and Bolbapium striatopunctatum (Castelnau, 1840) (black squares); (b). Bolbapium boillyi Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (white circles) and Bolbapium quadrispinosum (Luederwaldt, 1931) (black squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012128/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012132>
    dc:description "Figure 14. Geographical distribution. (a). Bolbapium dutraorum Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (black squares) and Bolbapium quinquestriatum (Boubomont, 1932) (white circles); (b). Bolbapium furtadoi Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (black circles) and Bolbapium matheusi Carvalho and Vazde-Mello, sp. nov. (white squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012132/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012136>
    dc:description "Figure 16. Geographical distribution. (a). Bolbapium minutum (Luederwaldt, 1931) (white circles); (b). Bolbapium paralucidulum Ide and Martínez, 1993 (white squares) and Bolbapium sergioidae Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (black circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012136/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012130>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Geographical distribution. (a). Bolbapium borgmeieri Martínez, 1976 (black squares) and Bolbapium sulcifrons Ide and Martínez, 1993 (white circles); (b). Bolbapium caesum (Klug, 1843) (white circles) and Bolbapium luederwaldti Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (black squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012130/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012108>
    dc:description "Figure 4. (a). Pronotum with robust bituberculated structure, connected at base and separated at the apex, Bolbapium quadrispinosum (Luederwaldt, 1931); (b). head with tranverse carina without tubercles, Bolbapium limeirai Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (c). head with tranverse carina with tubercles, Bolbapium furtadoi Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (d). head with tubercle adjacent to each eye, with base wider than apex,Bolbapium boillyi Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello,sp. nov.; (e). clypeal carina extending to the mid-frontal region and meeting in the central region, Bolbapium paralucidulum Ide and Martínez, 1993; (f). clypeal carina short, not reaching the midline region of the frons, Bolbapium lucidulum (Klug, 1843)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012108/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012134>
    dc:description "Figure 15. Geographical distribution. (a). Bolbapium limeirai Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (black circles) and Bolbapium howdeni Martínez, 1976 (white squares); (b). Bolbapium lucidulum (Klug, 1843) (white triangles), Bolbapium modestum (Castelnau, 1840) (white squares) and Bolbapium sampaioorum Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (black circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012134/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012110>
    dc:description "Figure 5. (a). Subpentagonal scutellum; (b). elongated scutellum, Bolbapium sulcifrons Ide and Martínez, 1993; (c). pronotum with smooth lateral margins; (d). pronotum with serrated lateral margins, Bolbapium quinquestriatum (Boucomont, 1932)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012110/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012114>
    dc:description "Figure 6. (a). Pronotum with almost rectangular structure, Bolbapium modestum (Castelnau, 1840); (b). head with tubercle adjacent to each eye, Bolbapium borgmeieri Martínez, 1976; (c). head without tubercles, Bolbapium matheusi Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (d). pronotum with curved structure towards the head, without angulations, Bolbapium howdeni Martínez, 1976; (e). head with tubercles wider than long; pronotum with rectangular structure, Bolbapium sampaioorum Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov.; (f). head with tubercle narrow adjacent to each eye; pronotum with curved structure, Bolbapium caesum (Klug, 1843)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012114/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012122>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Aedeagus. Bolbapium modestum (Castelnau, 1840) (a). dorsal view; (b). ventral view; (c). lateral view. Bolbapium parcepunctatum (Arrow, 1913) (d). dorsal view; (e). ventral view; (f). lateral view. Bolbapium santanaorum Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (g). dorsal view; (h). ventral view; (i). lateral view. Bolbapium borgmeieri Martínez, 1976 (j). dorsal view; (k). ventral view; (l). lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012122/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012140>
    dc:description "Figure 17. Geographical distribution. Bolbapium parcepunctatum (Arrow, 1913) (black squares) and Bolbapium santanaorum Carvalho and Vaz-de-Mello, sp. nov. (white circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012140/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

